# campaign-condition-system

The campaign condition system implements multi-stage reward triggering with sequential validation and dependency tracking.

Core Components:

1. Condition Trigger Engine (src/components/campaigns/ConditionBuilder.tsx)
Importance Score: 95
- Sequential condition chaining with dependency validation
- Support for manual, CRM event, and time-based triggers 
- Real-time condition evaluation with state tracking
- Integration with gift card reward pools
- Dynamic reward allocation based on completion criteria

2. Reward Distribution Logic (src/components/campaigns/ConditionTriggers.tsx)
Importance Score: 90
- Automated reward triggering based on completed conditions
- Multi-condition campaign management with sequential validation
- Gift card pool integration for fulfillment
- Delivery status tracking across channels
- Fallback handling for failed reward distribution

Business Rules:
- Conditions must be completed in defined sequence
- Previous condition completion required before next activation
- Real-time validation of reward pool availability
- Automatic reward distribution on condition completion
- Support for parallel and sequential condition paths
- Maximum 5 conditions per campaign sequence

Condition Types:
1. Manual Verification
- Agent approval required
- Supporting documentation options
- Notes/reason requirement for rejections

2. CRM Event Triggers
- Lead status changes
- Opportunity stage advancement
- Custom field updates
- Contact property changes

3. Time-Based Triggers
- Scheduled activation dates
- Duration-based conditions
- Cool-down periods between rewards
- Expiration handling

4. Call Center Triggers
- Call outcome based
- Duration thresholds
- Agent verification required
- Disposition code mapping

